column16: "Description": "The Inovelli Red Series Fan/Light Switch is a 700 Series Z-Wave in-wall fan + light switch that controls both your fan motor and its attached LED
column18: & Incandescent bulbs which can be highly customized to your liking at the switch itself with our unique config buttons and advanced firmware. In addition
column19: the Red Series comes with advanced features such as scene support
column23: etc. This is the first of its kind that allows homes that only have one wire coming from the fan to the light switch and uses both a light switch and canopy module. Inspired and worked on by our wonderful community."
column27: hold the light up or down button and press the Light on/off button three (3) times. Please Note: If this doesn't work
column28: you can check to see if your switch is within Z-Wave Range by holding down the Light Button for 5-10 seconds (if it's not within range
column29: the LED Bar will indicate Red and if it is within Range
column30: the LED Bar will indicate Green). If your switch indicates Red
column31: please move the switch closer to the HUB. If your switch indicates Green
column32: please try running an Exclusion to reset your switch."
column34: put your HUB in exclusion mode
column35: hold the light up or down button and press the Light on/off button three (3) times."
column36: "ResetHelp": "You may factory reset the switch by holding down the light up or down button and the light on/off button for twenty (20) or more seconds. The LED Bar will turn Red and blink three (3) times to confirm."

"Help": "This changes the speed in which the attached light dims up or down. A setting of 0 should turn the light immediately on or off (almost like an on/off switch). Increasing the value should slow down the transition speed. Range:0-98 Default: 4"

"Help": "This changes the speed in which the attached light dims up or down when controlled from the physical switch. A setting of 0 should turn the light immediately on or off (almost like an on/off switch). Increasing the value should slow down the transition speed. A setting of 99 should keep this in sync with parameter 1. Range:0-99 Default: 99"
"Help": "This changes the speed in which the attached light turns on or off. For example
column17: when a user sends the switch a basicSet(value: 0xFF) or basicSet(value: 0x00)
column18: this is the speed in which those actions take place. A setting of 0 should turn the light immediately on or off (almost like an on/off switch). Increasing the value should slow down the transition speed. A setting of 99 should keep this in sync with parameter 1. Range:0-99 Default: 99"

column16: "Help": "This changes the speed in which the attached light turns on or off from the physical switch. For example
column17: when a user presses the up or down button
column18: this is the speed in which those actions take place. A setting of 0 should turn the light immediately on or off (almost like an on/off switch). Increasing the value should slow down the transition speed. A setting of 99 should keep this in sync with parameter 1. Range:0-99 Default: 99"
